The paper discusses a new model family and algorithm for learning fast mixing models for structured prediction. This involves developing a method to control the mixing times of Markov Chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) algorithms, which are commonly used for approximate inference in machine learning. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning)
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence)
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms)
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks)
- cs.CL (Computation and Language)
